bits.name: protocol
bits.description: Input correction data protocol: 0: Unknown, 1: RTCM3, 2: SPARTN (Safe Position Augmentation for Real Time Navigation), 30: UBX-RXM-QZSSL6

bits.name: errStatus
bits.description: Error status of the received correction message content based on possibly available error codes or checksums: 0: Unknown, 1: Error-free, 2: Erroneous

bits.name: msgUsed
bits.description: Status of receiver using the input message: 0: Unknown, 1: Not used, 2: Used

bits.name: correctionId
bits.description: Identifier for the correction stream: For RTCM 3: Reference station ID (DF003) of the received RTCM input message. Valid range 0-4095. Reported only for the standard RTCM messages that include the DF003 field and for the u-blox proprietary RTCM messages 4072.x. For all other messages, reports 0xFFFF. For other correction types 0xFFFF.

bits.name: msgTypeValid
bits.description: Validity of the msgType field. Set to False e.g. if the protocol does not define msgType.

bits.name: msgSubTypeValid
bits.description: Validity of the msgSubType field. Set to False e.g. if the protocol does not define subtype for the msgType.

bits.name: msgInputHandle
bits.description: 0=Receiver does not have input handling support for this message, 1=Receiver has input handling support for this message. Input handling support does not necessitate that message is supported/used by the receiver.

bits.name: msgEncrypted
bits.description: Encryption status of the input message: 0: Unknown, 1: Not encrypted, 2: Encrypted

bits.name: msgDecrypted
bits.description: Decryption status of the input message: 0: Unknown, 1: Not decrypted, 2: Decrypted
